----------------------------Welcome to the HMDesk----------------------------------------
We are so happy to have you here! This is a project based in Python and Django, 
designed for the people who want to manage their own money. We work hard to 
build a very flexible and estructured aplicattion. Their so many functions 
to rework the billings and spending like, Manage Expenses, Manage Income and estructured

@For the Developers

Zero Step - Starting day

- PS C:\Users\Desktop\Desktop\Pastas\HMDesk> cd hmdesk
- PS C:\Users\Desktop\Desktop\Pastas\HMDesk\hmdesk> pipenv shell 

First Step - Config the environment

- Open powershell
- pip install pipenv
- cd the folder that will recive your project
- pipenv install django
- django-admin startproject hmdesk
- pipenv shell (open terminal powershell) in the terminal of VSCode
- cd your project folder
- ALLWAYS USE THIS COMMAND IN THE FOLDER OF APPLICAITON: python manage.py runserver

- Will generate the link for your website EX: "Starting development server at http://127.0.0.1:8000/"

Second Step - Donwload Postgres
- Donwload and install (password = AQfk5VNsW=)
- Open PgAdmin4
- Create Database
- Trocar as configs no settings.py DATABASE
- Terminal: pipenv install psycopg2
DATABASES = {
    'default': {
        'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.postgresql',
        'NAME': 'hmdeskdb',
        'USER': 'postgres',
        'PASSWORD': 'AQfk5VNsW=',
        'HOST':'localhost',
    }
}

Third Step - After configurate all the static files
- Create de Apps for the application EX: python manage.py startapp Expenses
- After that go to the settings.py and add the app into INSTALLED_APPS


Fourth Step - Working with URL
- Add to the project folder urls.py
- Make the base config
    from django.urls import path
    from . import views
    urlpatterns = {
        path('',views.what_view,name="name_you_want")
    }
- add to the main project urls.py project the app url

Fifth Step - GitConfig
install pipenv install django-heroku
install pipenv install gunicorn
- Make the settings configuration
    import django.heroku 
    django.heroku.settings(locals())
- Create file in hmdesk "Procfile"

(Sequence to Create an App)

1- Make the command python manage.py startapp blablablabla
2- Create Template Folder 
3- Inside the TemplateFolder create the Views.html
4- Make the urls
5- The Views
6- Put in the main settings views the url

If does not work use this on settings.py
STATIC_ROOT=os.path.join(BASE_DIR, 'static')

